{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8588369d-64a4-4b00-a1ff-a4c6273c5880","content":"There's no repo content here, so here's a general migration guide:\n\n**Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`** using the `DotNetCoreCLI@2` task (or a script step). Microsoft.Testing.Platform is invoked via `dotnet test` — there's no dedicated Azure DevOps task for it.\n\n### Key changes\n\n**1. Enable the new platform** in each test `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**2. Replace the pipeline task:**\n\nBefore (VSTest@3):\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testSelector: 'testAssemblies'\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\nAfter (DotNetCoreCLI@2 or script):\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Why the extra publish tasks?\n`VSTest@3` auto-published results and coverage. With `dotnet test` you must explicitly publish TRX files (`PublishTestResults@2`) and coverage (`PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`).\n\n### Checklist\n- Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` NuGet if TRX isn't generated automatically\n- Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` NuGet for coverage\n- Use `condition: always()` on publish tasks so results appear even on test failure\n- Remove any `<IsTestProject>` overrides that might conflict","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8a2b0994-6732-4cf1-a4b7-d786ddf8ed0c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty. This is a general knowledge question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":692,"requestId":"7C1D:21DC3D:25A0459:29ADC05:69F93F35"},"id":"809425c4-0860-44a9-a240-f66f42129838","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:52:19.686Z","parentId":"eeedd99c-b77e-4875-9d26-b23ac4656a89"}
